position - absolute vs realtive

the elements stay in the normal document flow u cna move it using top left right bottom.
syntax .box-name{
    l:something; etc
}
it moves to its original position
.box{
    position:relative;
    top:20px;
    left:20 px;
}
other element do not move into this space
use case - if u want to move some element slightyl do the relative part


now absolute 
the element is removed from the normal doc flow
position relative to nesarest position ie: parent ke relative hogi

eg
.child{
    pos:rel;
    top:10;
    l:20px;
}
element will move freely kahin bhi on basis of parent

use cases : popups, icon buttons.


